1.2 The term "Proprietary Data" encompasses all technical knowledge, manufacturing processes, recipes, specifications, manuals (including maintenance, parts, and service), data sheets, sales and technical bulletins, customer lists, marketing strategies, pricing details, cost information, promotional materials such as filmstrips and recordings, and any other documents or information related to the development, production, distribution, and commercialization of the AuraGen and/or the Products. Additionally, it includes any information disclosed under this Agreement during its execution, which is marked as confidential or whose confidential nature is apparent from the circumstances surrounding its disclosure. Proprietary Data does not include information that:

   (i) was publicly available before the disclosure by the provider;
   (ii) becomes publicly available after disclosure by the provider, excluding situations where this occurs due to a breach or failure to fulfill obligations by the recipient;
   (iii) was in the possession of the recipient without restrictions on use or disclosure prior to the disclosure by the provider, as demonstrated by the recipient's records and files at that time;
   (iv) is obtained lawfully and without restrictions on use or disclosure from a third party, without breaching their obligations of confidentiality; or
   (v) is developed independently by the recipient without reference to the provider's Proprietary Data, as evidenced by the recipient's records and files.
